Example datasets

exampleTreeData.Rd

Data sets given to illustrate input data structures.

Format

Tree data corresponding to three forest plots. Data frame with 40 rows (tree records) and columns:

  • ID: Forest plot code, defined as the combination of province code and "estadillo".

  • Species: Tree species code.

  • N: Tree density (individuals per hectare) that the record represents.

  • DBH: Tree diameter at breast height (cm).

  • H: Tree height (m)
